<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_fdd10516-cf3a-433f-bd31-03aaf673b38d" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="NT"><sptc>13.4.5</sptc><title id="_259864ea-f2ad-482e-ac9d-88a18f405fab">Exhaust fans</title><archive-num>New for 2022</archive-num><subclause id="_9d097b2a-05a0-4782-8df6-8609e2c7d20e" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_fdf84cb3-0e59-4445-afaa-841b0bb4287b">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>An exhaust fan must be fitted with a sealing device such as a self-closing damper, filter or the like when serving a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1225_1.8.0.xml#_6f4c27ea-b6b3-468c-9ff4-72d533d9d0a2" id="_0e605d83-dd5f-4881-93f8-28a5548ccf65" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">conditioned space</xref>.</p></subclause><callout id="_e50fa017-2033-46df-9882-c456722644a6"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>An exhaust fan is considered to be adequately sealed if it is fitted with a filter such as the type commonly used in kitchen range hoods.</p></callout></clause>